ser</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/02 10:45:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23239.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Looking for some input on a new class...</span><hr size=1> I've played a rogue and warrior to 60, and I'm switching servers now to try something new.  Looking for some input on the best class to level to 60 that is usefull on raids and reasonable to level starting at level 1 with no gear or connections on the server -- taking into both ease of leveling and use in the end game.  Thanks.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugupwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gupwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/10/02 12:03:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23239.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looking for some input on a new class...</span><hr size=1> /shrug<br><br>Guess I'd have to say monk if you're looking for a melee, and probably a druid if you're looking in the caster direction. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzemenartheexiled.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zemenar the Exiled</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/10/02 12:24:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23239.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looking for some input on a new class...</span><hr size=1> Enchanter comes to mind. Easy to lvl since everyone will want you, good support role in raids as well. But really you should choose one based on preference afterall, what good is playing a class you'll be lvling up if you hate it? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uccorndog.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ccorndog</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/10/02 12:28:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23239.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looking for some input on a new class...</span><hr size=1> I would have to vote against druid (even though I have one) there are a lot of gaps when druids are just not useful raid situations.  A shaman I've found to be a very powerful class and quite easy to level.  Barb shamans have high str and sta which of course makes it easy at the younger levels, easy class to solo once you get your 39 pet and 39 slow.  The everfrost area is also quite rich with drops for a char with no plat, SoWing for donations from level 9+ until you get on your feet also helps, and selling SoW potions is nice profit.  The shaman + monk combo is time tested to be awesome and since monks don't normally loot that leaves more cash for the shaman.  Powerleveled a shaman on my GF's account and my monk has never been happier <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>As far as starting out, we've discussed how to get cash, Jar Jar drops in KC are rotting away all the time, by the mid 30s (or level 1 for that matter) a shaman should have no problems sitting in KC /ooc'ing to loot jar jar pieces.  <br><br>If you do decide to play an evil class I would go for an ikky shaman, the PoH iksar only shaman drops are very nice compared to the non-iksar drops.  <br><br>Then at your higher levels all the melee will love ya <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    haste, slow, hp, str, dex, sta, agi, ac, DD, dots, pets, potions... the list goes on.  I can't think of a time when a shaman isn't wanted in a group, especially a melee heavy group.<br><br>Just my 2cp<br><br><br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Edit: Please read our sig/personal pic rules. - ShadowCross</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushadowcross.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shadowcross</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_purplespot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 4/10/02 6:20:08 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uberethebard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bere the Bard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/10/02 12:53:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23239.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.btinternet.com/~j.doyle/computer/bardstale/BARD.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looking for some input on a new class...</span><hr size=1> No gear or connections is a hard one ... but having levelled 2 characters up to 60 you certainly know the ropes and can probably play any charecter up in levels swiftly.<br><br>I noticed you played 2 strong melee charecters.<br>Playing any &quot;weak&quot; class that needs to med a lot is going to suck for you. This includes clerics, enchanters , wizards, beastmasters, mages and shaman. <br>You want a charecter particularly useful in the end game so that leaves out necros and druids.<br>Bards, Paladins and Shadowknights all overhyped hybrids that suffer from not being able to do the pure damage a rogue or warrior can. (dps envy)<br><br>I guess that leaves monks ... but without a Fungi you are going to be the saddest monk on a server where everyones second toon is a leaping lizard.<br><br>If I neglected to offend your class, i apologise <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Edit</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Oh ... I left out rangers.  Your criteria was level swiftly and useful in raids? Is it any wonder I forgot them? Haha <br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uberethebard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bere the Bard</A> at: 4/10/02 1:01:04 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uweoden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Weoden</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/10/02 1:33:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23239.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~craigdphilips/rosephoto.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looking for some input on a new class...</span><hr size=1> yea, chanter or cleric or wizard are the best bets.  those three are desired in the high end.  Particuarly clerics. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uweoden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Weoden</A> at: 4/10/02 1:33:30 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard