tyle="font-family: Century Gothic; font-size: 14px; color: #FFFFFF; background-color: #000000"><option>                  Hedii</option><option>  Rogue of the 47th Season</option><option>    Crusaders of the Realm</option><option>           The Nameless</option></select></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uacutex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Acutex</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/11/02 12:18:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23239.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looking for some input on a new class...</span><hr size=1> The point of my post was actually to get some input on classes that are *easy* to level naked that are still usefull.  I have no idea how difficult it is to level classes other than my own because I don't play them.  If you are interested in actually getting some facts as to whether or not I have leveled a rogue and a warrior to 60, feel free to email me at amsteleq@hotmail.com and I will arrange an in-game meeting with you!  If not, shut your mouth.  Kk, thx~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elegance>Elegance</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/11/02 12:30:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23239.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looking for some input on a new class...</span><hr size=1> shaman are powerful right out of the box. if you go barb you have a sweet starting area that will have you paying for your own way and pre pirchaseing your spells by lvl 9.<br><br>just read up on the newbie quests in the zone. <br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukealios.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kealios</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/11/02 11:22:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23239.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> My experiences</span><hr size=1> Ive got a ton of characters, mostly cause I get bored easy and so I like to bounce around.<br><br>I have a 51 iksar shaman that I love, and was the first of my 8 to break lvl 30.  Once I got to the point that I could start getting some cool gear, I realized (hiindsight is always 20-20) that I think I would rather have made a troll shaman.  Yea, beginning wis may be a little lower, but having reached 51, I have compensated for that already.  What my iksar doesnt have that the troll could have is the darkness neck quest piece (Neriak?) and the JBB.  Same regen, but soloability isnt the same.  Oh well.<br><br>Love my 51 rogue.  She is also climbing fairly well, and will be my highest character soon, i think.<br><br>Ive got a ranger and shadow knight and bard, all in mid-20's.  None of them quite rock my boat.<br><br>Necro is a great solo class but blah, i HATE soloing for extended periods of time...and damn hard to get a group with misinformed people...<br><br>Beastlord?  I should just delete my lvl 7 BL...worthless imho.<br><br>My first ever character was my mage, and the first to hit 30.  BORING...even though mages have some cool utility spells, I shoulda made a wizzie.  Yea, I'd have to deal with all the requests for ports, but if Im gunna nuke, might as well do it right...<br><br>All of my characters have done decently well with little eq.  As my shaman got higher, and then my rogue, I was slowly able to start handing out little pieces of eq to my guys, but I think the casters would be the easiest.  A smaller mana pool just means you conserve mana a little more in combat...<br><br>My humble opinion,<br>Mookealiol Sunspear<br>Chukamuka Akumasomkuti<br>Rodcet Nife <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaxterixenobelix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Axterix EnObelix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/11/02 12:14:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23239.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My experiences</span><hr size=1> Don't bother with enchanter if you intend to go for a raid heavy guild.  Odds are they've got plenty and you'll just wind up doing what most of us do already... make a melee, cleric, or wizard alt.<br><br>More enchanters aren't needed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uiristreedawn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iris Treedawn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/11/02 12:43:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23239.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looking for some input on a new class...</span><hr size=1> I would recommend either a monk or a shaman.  Both are very useful in raids, and don't need much in the way of equipment to be powerful.  <br><br>Shaman don't have much downtime, with canni and regen.  And since they are constantly re-gaining mana, they don't need huge amounts of wisdom to be useful.<br><br>People twink alt monks like crazy, but they honestly don't need it!  A monk in cloth armor with nothing but their fists is doing fine, and there are inexpensive upgrades available.  For example - keep an eye out for a Cured Tizmak Tunic.  Not too heavy, and best ac you'll find until 50+!  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=shourt>Shourt </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/11/02 3:13:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23239.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1>  2 60s and u still cant decide? =p<br> ide have to go with enchanter myself =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucrydeeossiriand.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crydee Ossiriand</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/11/02 3:22:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23239.topic&index=14>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://questing-ranger.com/images/archer-2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looking for some input on a new 